# {{NAME}} — project skill (project-with-reflect)

State dir: `{{PDIR}}`
- `lessons/` — the project's **persistent knowledge of every kind**, as **flat, descriptively-named
  md files** (no imposed subfolders): practices & must-follow rules (`writing-rules.md`), settled
  conclusions, taxonomies, **experiment / baseline records** (`experiment-GUAVA.md`,
  `experiment-baseline.md`), research reports, a review format (`review-format.md`), reference/resource
  notes (a useful paper, a URL), and whatever else accrues. The model names + splits them wisely (split a
  long one; readability rules). **Exception — a lesson with artifacts is a folder note:** when a lesson
  embeds images/files it becomes `lessons/<name>/<name>.md` with its artifacts as siblings in
  `lessons/<name>/` (e.g. `lessons/experiment-GUAVA/experiment-GUAVA.md` + its `*.png`) — **never scatter
  a lesson's images flat in `lessons/`**. A lesson's **update style follows its nature**, which the model infers:
  - most are **distilled** — bounded-updated (add facts, fix wrong ones), loaded on demand.
  - some **accumulate** — an experiment-run log, a running results table: **append-only**, so the history
    (and numbers that host outputs later prune) is never lost or rewritten.
  `reflect` archives only the working `log.md` — **never a lesson**. See the `record` action for how new
  findings land here and **follow the format of the lesson they continue**.
- `workstreams/<workstream>/` — per workstream: `stream.json` (state) + `log.md` (granular history) +
  `<workstream>.md` (folder note = the **goal/plan log**: dated `### <date>` + ```` ```goal ```` / ```` ```plan ````
  blocks, newest-first; see *Working*).
- `decisions.md` — ideas tried / chosen / rejected (+ datasets, settings).
- `{{NAME}}.md` — the human dashboard / folder note (regenerated on reflect); also carries the
  project's `## TODO` backlog (see the `todo` action).
- `evals/<eval>/` — each eval is a **folder note** `<eval>/<eval>.md` (the case spec) + its input files
  (images / fixtures) as siblings. `tasks/<task>.md`, `config.json`.

This skill is self-contained: its `SKILL.md` works even without the meta-skill installed. When the
meta-skill IS installed, prefer its helpers in the active agent's user skill directory
(`~/.claude/skills/project-with-reflect/scripts/` for Claude Code,
`~/.codex/skills/project-with-reflect/scripts/` for Codex) for deterministic ops.

**Codebase roots.** `config.json` carries `location` (`local` | `remote`) and `roots[]` (the working
dirs — a project can span several, e.g. an app repo + a sibling dataset repo; if `roots` is absent the
single `repo` is the only root). For a **remote** project the code lives on `host_connection` (an ssh
connection): operate it **through `/<host_connection>`** (run / build / test over its alias — contract rule 5),
and remember **your cwd here (the vault workstream) is not the repo's working dir** — each root `path` is a
dir *on the host*. Never assume a local checkout; load `roots` for the real paths. Version workstreams on a
remote project are **lineage-only automatically** — `register-workstream` degrades a `worktree` / `in-repo`
workstream to `tracked` (those git realizations need a local checkout); make a real branch on the host
yourself if you want one. (Local single-root projects: `roots` is just the one repo,
`location: local` — nothing extra to think about.)

